This paper focuses on improving the quality of conversations in online communities using deep learning models, which falls under the category of natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the social impact of online conversations, which could be related to social and information networks (cs.SI) and social computing (cs.SD). The proposed model involves attention mechanisms, which could be related to computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of the study for improving user experience, which could be related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
